00:02:50.560 --> 00:02:52.610
How can we truly replace an image?

00:02:54.790 --> 00:02:58.530
So now just to go through some
of the top five alt text errors

00:02:58.530 --> 00:03:01.970
that we see most commonly
occurring on the web.

00:03:01.970 --> 00:03:04.960
The first is keyword stuffing.

00:03:04.960 --> 00:03:08.780
This technique is really primarily
for SEO purposes, it seems,

00:03:08.780 --> 00:03:10.860
because it's not all
that descriptive.

00:03:10.860 --> 00:03:14.610
It involves actually just
putting in a list of keywords

00:03:14.610 --> 00:03:18.750
to maybe rank higher in search
results, and here's an example I have

00:03:18.750 --> 00:03:22.590
on the slide here for the
photo that's represented.

00:03:24.510 --> 00:03:28.030
Person, rainbow wig, bold, makeup.
These might be keywords

00:03:28.030 --> 00:03:30.530
that someone might search for
this image, but they don't belong

00:03:30.530 --> 00:03:32.590
in alt text because they're
not all that descriptive.

00:03:33.610 --> 00:03:36.318
We also see a lot of
overly-simplistic descriptions

00:03:36.319 --> 00:03:39.010
that kind
of all blend together.

00:03:39.010 --> 00:03:41.430
So that might look something
like, for this image, a person

00:03:41.430 --> 00:03:42.190
with colorful hair.

00:03:42.190 --> 00:03:44.340
It doesn't tell us a lot
about what's going on.

00:03:45.790 --> 00:03:49.210
We also see some really bad examples
of image file names making it

00:03:49.210 --> 00:03:54.500
into the alt text, just a string
of random words or numbers,

00:03:54.500 --> 00:03:57.670
just copying the file name
right into the alt text.

00:03:59.100 --> 00:04:00.520
Formulate descriptions.

00:04:00.520 --> 00:04:02.120
This is a big one.

00:04:02.120 --> 00:04:07.950
So this involves some sort of
combination of different terms

00:04:07.950 --> 00:04:10.330
or components.

00:04:10.330 --> 00:04:15.320
For example, product plus title
plus color equals alt text.

00:04:15.320 --> 00:04:17.957
So in this case,
if we were advertising the wig

00:04:17.958 --> 00:04:20.842
this person's wearing,
it might say something

00:04:20.843 --> 00:04:23.600
like Long wavy rainbow
wig, heat resistant.

00:04:23.600 --> 00:04:24.130
Right?

00:04:24.130 --> 00:04:27.430
So something that seems kind
of awkwardly product related

00:04:27.431 --> 00:04:28.530
in the alt text.

00:04:29.960 --> 00:04:31.550
Finally, we have AI-generated.

00:04:31.550 --> 00:04:35.790
So a lot of the AI-generated
alt text really stands out

00:04:35.790 --> 00:04:39.620
as either inaccurate or incomplete,
like someone hasn't actually reviewed

00:04:39.620 --> 00:04:40.830
that alt text.

00:04:40.830 --> 00:04:43.300
So here’s just a few common
errors that we're seeing out there

00:04:43.300 --> 00:04:47.430
on the web contributing to
