<v Caroline> It's a great point.

00:47:17.220 --> 00:47:21.870
We do need to continuously make
sure that the image descriptions

00:47:21.870 --> 00:47:25.110
that we're writing,
we're getting direct feedback

00:47:25.110 --> 00:47:28.300
from screen-reader
users, from blind users.

00:47:28.300 --> 00:47:30.890
Is this information
actually getting across?

00:47:30.890 --> 00:47:34.760
So it's really important to make
sure to collect that information

00:47:34.760 --> 00:47:39.360
from your users to get
that understanding.

00:47:39.360 --> 00:47:43.850
But, you know, leaning on different
techniques for image description,

00:47:43.850 --> 00:47:48.550
not just describing the basics.

00:47:48.550 --> 00:47:51.120
